    {
      "id": "e08a62bc1c1ae142555bbbf409f1586a33d7542a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-12-18 14:35:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI doubt this patch could resolve the issue, caller of kiblnd_connect_peer() should have reference of this peer. At the meanwhile, kiblnd_peer_decref() called by kiblnd_connect_peer() is supposed to release the reference taken within this function, so I think it is safe to call it in any order as long as the caller has another refcount on this peer.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
